original: Lindberg, Albert Hugo, tandläkare, Norrköping, f. 23/3/84 i Norrköping av kass. Albert Fredrik L. o. Oscara Mousquette. G. 16 m. Estrid Maria Zetterlund. Barn: Gösta f. 18. — Mog:ex. i Norrköping 02, landl:kand. 03, tandläkare 07. Assist, i Dresden o. Wien 0’8-09, praktik i Norrköping sed. 09, förest, f. Norrköpings folksk. tandpoliklin. 14-27. Ordf. i östergötl. läns tandlifören. 21-22, 28-31 o. 37-39, i Norrköpings tandl :sällsk. 25-27 o. 33-35, hed :led. där sed. 45, led. av stads-fullm. 28-30.
translated: Lindberg, Albert Hugo, dentist, Norrköping, b. 23/3/84 in Norrköping to cashier Albert Fredrik L. and Oscara Mousquette. Married on 16th with Estrid Maria Zetterlund. Children: Gösta b. 18. — Completed military service in Norrköping in 1902, graduated landowner candidate in 1903, became a dentist in 1907. Worked as an assistant in Dresden and Vienna from 1908-1909, practiced in Norrköping since 1909, served as head of the dental clinic at Norrköpings peoples school from 1914-1927. Served as chairman of the Östergötland county dental association from 1921-1922, 1928-1931, and 1937-1939, and the Norrköpings dental society from 1925-1927 and 1933-1935, currently an honorary member since 1945. Served as a member of the city council from 1928-1930.
